Namespace 

It is a programming object that defines the scope for a set of clases and instances .It is essentially a container or enviroment where WMI provider classers are defined and  managed. Namespaces are used to organise classes that represents differnt managed environment. Provies a hierarchical organisation  of classes.

A Namespace organizes information similar to folders in a filesystem. The top “folder” of the WMI namespace is always called “root”.

Default namespace : Root/Default

