WMI arbitartor 

WMI arbitrator is a component of WMI servivce that manages scheduling and execution of tasks received from WMI client process 

It resides in the WMISVChost.exe and is implemented as the following static singleton instance : Wbemcore! cwmiarbitrator ::m_Parb

The arbitartor track queries and incoming client requests as tasks of object type : Wbemcore!cwmittask().

Examples of some information tracked for these tasks include Client process id , Clilent computername , Last client activity, WQL text query  , Task submission etc.

Results returned by executing these tasks retrieved from WMI provider processes, are held directly in WINMGMT SVChost.exe heap memory until retrived by clients .

If the client does not spcify WBEM_FLAG_FORWARD_ONLY to indiacte a non rewindable or single direction enumerator , then the complete result set will reamin in WINMGMT heap memory for 20 minutes .

Event IP 5858 : WMI_Activity/Operational

Generated for cancellation of idle task.

* The 20 minutes max idle timeout can be overidden by the following DWORD registry value : HKLM\SOFTWARE\MICROSOFT\WBEM\CIMOM\Arbtask MaxIdle(Default = on 1200000ms)


WMI throttling 

WMI Arbitrator throttling is a forced thread sleep state that occurs when the total amount of tracked task memory (m_utotal Memoryusage) reaches the throttling limit (m_uSystemhigh)which defaults to 256MB.





